            <p>The Department of Anaesthesiology is providing Anaesthetic services to both emergency and elective surgical , obstetric , orthopaedic as well as ENT and Ophthalmological surgeries from the inception of the Hospital. There are presently Seven Operating Theatres with four on the third floor with four on the fourth floor to be made operational shortly and three ICUâ€™s namely the Medical ICU ,Respiratory ICU and the Surgical ICU situated on the second floor. Intensive Care of the patients requiring Ventilator and Hemodynamic support in the ICUs are lead by a dynamic team from the department which also manages Emergency trauma care in the Casualty.</p>
            <p>On an average more than 400 major surgeries are performed per month in the Modular operating rooms which have HEPA filters to provide Laminar air flows to reduce the risk of infection. The patient is assessed  preoperatively by an Anaesthesiologist at the pre-anaesthetic clinic , the risk stratification and optimisation is done before the surgery is scheduled . </p>
            <p>Post operative manangement is done by our team to look after postsurgical care, acute pain management  and monitoring .Pain clinic out patient services are also being provided for the treatment of Chronic pain .</p>
            <p>The department has one Associate Professor ,three Assistant Professors ,three Specialists and ten Senior Residents providing  round the clock emergency cover , every day of the year for the Surgical and Intensive and Emergency care services .Academic activities include the organisation of CMEs twice a year ,conducting work shops and several research studies with Institutional Ethics Committee clearance. Several of the completed studies have also been published in reputed journals.</p>
